01/11/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- During talks Friday (29 October) with European Commission delegation head Michael Humphreys, Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic reiterated that his government is committed to improving co-operation with The Hague tribunal. The two met to discuss the pace of reforms in RS and BiH as well as the remaining tasks under the EC Feasibility Study for BiH. 
In other news, Federation of BiH Interior Minister Mevludin Halilovic said Sunday that negotiations on the future police structure in BiH are continuing. He described last week's visit to Brussels by the BiH police restructuring commission members as informational, and said no concrete agreements had been reached yet. (Fena, NTV Hayat - 31/10/04; Fena, RS government Web site - 29/10/04) 
